            <a:r>
              <a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/>
              <a:t>The 19 specialist RAG tools are created by make_all_rag_tools() and backed directly by PostgreSQL — they bypass the high-level RAG agent tool pipeline. This gives agents much finer control. For example: resolve_document uses fuzzy matching to find actual doc_id from 'the safety policy'. fetch_chunk_window gets a chunk plus its neighbors, perfect for expanding context. compare_clauses extracts matching clause numbers from two docs side by side — great for version comparisons. diff_documents gives structural diffs based on which clauses exist in each. The graph search tools are optional — if the graph store isn't configured, they return a helpful message. Tools also include scratchpad_write/read/list for agents to maintain session state. Full LangChain tool system, so composable with everything else.</a:t>
            </a:r>
          </a:p>
